class Solution {
    public int distanceTraveled(int mainTank, int additionalTank) {
        int distance = 0;
        while (mainTank > 0 || additionalTank >= 1) {
            if (mainTank >= 5) {
                mainTank -= 5;
                distance += 50;
            } else {
                if (additionalTank >= 1) {
                    mainTank++;
                    additionalTank--;
                    distance += 10;
                } else {
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return distance;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(min(mainTank, additionalTank))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iteratively simulates fuel consumption and transfer. It prioritizes using fuel from the main tank and utilizes the additional tank for replenishment when the main tank is low. The loop terminates when both tanks are empty, ensuring efficient processing.

